parts:
Your previous extraction had validation errors:

JSON SCHEMA ERRORS:
  - payload.fields.5.data_type: 'X8' is not valid under any of the given schemas

Please fix these issues and return the corrected JSON.
The corrected response must conform to the schema provided earlier.
IMPORTANT: Make sure every byte of the payload is accounted for by fields.

fields.name: iTOW
fields.description: GPS time of week of the navigation epoch. See the section iTOW timestamps in Integration manual for details.

fields.name: gpsFix
fields.description:
GPSfix Type, this value does not qualify a fix as valid and within the limits. See note on flag gpsFixOk below.
0x00 = no fix
0x01 = dead reckoning only
0x02 = 2D-fix
0x03 = 3D-fix
0x04 = GPS + dead reckoning combined
0x05 = Time only fix
0x06..0xff = reserved

bits.name: gpsFixOk
bits.description: 1 = position and velocity valid and within DOP and ACC Masks.

bits.name: wknSet
bits.description: 1 = Week Number valid (see section Time validity in Integration manual for details)

bits.name: towSet
bits.description: 1 = Time of Week valid (see section Time validity in Integration manual for details)

bits.name: mapMatching
bits.description:
map matching status:
00: none
01: valid but not used, i.e. map matching data was received, but was too old
10: valid and used, map matching data was applied
11: valid and used, map matching data was applied. In case of sensor unavailability map matching data enables dead reckoning. This requires map matched latitude/longitude or heading data.

bits.name: psmState
bits.description:
power save mode state (not supported for protocol versions less than 13.01)
0 = ACQUISITION [or when psm disabled]
1 = TRACKING
2 = POWER OPTIMIZED TRACKING
3 = INACTIVE

bits.name: spoofDetState
bits.description:
Spoofing detection state (not supported for protocol versions less than 18.00)
0: Unknown or deactivated
1: No spoofing indicated
2: Spoofing indicated
3: Multiple spoofing indications
